stylometry:
Simulation models incorporate uncertainty into one or more variables. It allows the user to see how the outputs would vary as a function of the given inputs. It also shows how sensitive a particular system is to a change in operating conditions. This helps the business answer what if questions without physically changing things within the process before seeing if it is worth time and money. 

We would use simulation models to help us figure out what would happen if a certain input changed, or if the market changed, or if cost changed, etc. You can change the cost on the simulation spreadsheet and see what it could potentially do to your business, whether it is good, bad, or indifferent.
